{"source_key":"sha256-936c2255c014a3b570a20fd4a59cd922","record_index":115,"record_hash":"sha256:c64df6b32f6bff8327261f24245ab5262878ef22b90e1fd1467197d0cfee87aa","timestamp":"2026-05-19T20:34:41.654Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: f6c882\nWall time: 0.8823 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1300\nOutput:\n{\"data\":{\"repository\":{\"pullRequest\":{\"number\":13371,\"url\":\"https://github.com/gitbutlerapp/gitbutler/pull/13371\",\"title\":\"gitbutler.noShadow git config removes macos shadow\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOI4EVGc7-xcg9\",\"body\":\"@schacon we are likely better off putting this config in `UiSettings` in `crates/but-settings/src/app_settings.rs` similar to `use_native_title_bar`.\\r\\nThe function `create` in `crates/gitbutler-tauri/src/window.rs` already has the settings loaded there, checking `use_native_title_bar` so `no_shadow` can be just like it. \\r\\nYou can then set it via `~/Library/Application\\\\ Support/gitbutler/settings.json` \\r\\n\\r\\nThere's a plan to migrate the app settings to a dedicated gitconfig file at some point in the future but haven't been able to prioritize it, and it's nicer to keep it consistent for now. Plus we avoid introducing libgi2 \",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-18T19:02:56Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-18T19:02:56Z\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"krlvi\"}},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOI4EVGc8AAAABC4RT_A\",\"body\":\"@krlvi is this better?\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-19T13:24:15Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-19T13:24:15Z\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"schacon\"}}]},\"reviews\":{\"nodes\":[{\"id\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"body\":\"## Pull request overview\\n\\nAdds a macOS-specific toggle to disable the Tauri window shadow based on a user Git config key (`gitbutler.noShadow`), allowing runtime UI behavior changes via Git configuration.\\n\\n**Changes:**\\n- Introduces a macOS-only helper to read `gitbutler.noShadow` from Git config.\\n- Applies the config-derived value to the Tauri window builder via `.shadow(!no_shadow)`.\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-04-18T08:48:09Z\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"copilot-pull-request-reviewer\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDOI4EVGc8AAAABAXSDuA\",\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"body\":\"## Pull request overview\\n\\nCopilot reviewed 5 out of 6 changed files in this pull request and generated 3 comments.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-05-\n[TRUNCATED]\nI4EVGc7CtTIP\",\"body\":\"The docs for `no_shadow` say it affects \\\"the main window\\\", but `gitbutler_tauri::window::create()` is used for both the main window and per-project windows on macOS (e.g. `crates/gitbutler-tauri/src/projects.rs`), so this setting will apply to all windows created via that helper. Consider updating the wording to avoid implying it only affects a single window.\\n\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-19T13:28:20Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-19T13:28:21Z\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"copilot-pull-request-reviewer\"}}]}},{\"id\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"isResolved\":false,\"isOutdated\":false,\"path\":\"crates/but-settings/assets/defaults.jsonc\",\"line\":77,\"diffSide\":\"RIGHT\",\"startLine\":77,\"startDiffSide\":null,\"originalLine\":77,\"originalStartLine\":null,\"resolvedBy\":null,\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"id\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"body\":\"The comment says this setting skips the drop shadow for the \\\"main window\\\", but on macOS the `noShadow` flag is applied in `window::create()` and therefore affects all windows created via that helper (main + per-project windows). Updating this comment to match actual behavior would prevent confusion.\\n\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-19T13:28:21Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-19T13:28:21Z\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"copilot-pull-request-reviewer\"}}]}},{\"id\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"isResolved\":false,\"isOutdated\":false,\"path\":\"crates/gitbutler-tauri/src/window.rs\",\"line\":277,\"diffSide\":\"RIGHT\",\"startLine\":